          {
            "text": "Welcome to the second study of this chapter! \n\nIn this study, we'll cover a game from the 1971 Candidates Quarterfinal match between Robert James Fischer and Mark Taimanov held in Vancouver, Canada. \n\nIt was a six-game match, this is the fourth game and the score is 3-0 for Fischer (spoiler: Bobby won 6-0).\n\nBobby with the white pieces managed to trade the rooks and entered this endgame, where he is left with a light-squared bishop against the knight. \n\nLet's see how White managed to win this game with razor-sharp precision!!",
            "arrows": null,
            "highlights": null
